---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import profileImage from '../assets/profile.png';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import ProjectCard from '../components/ProjectCard.astro';
import OtherContributions from '../components/OtherContributions.astro';
---

<Layout title="Beege's Portfolio">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="min-h-[70vh] flex items-center">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 md:gap-12">
      <div class="flex-1 order-2 md:order-1">
        <p class="text-primary font-mono mb-4">Hi, I'm</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold mb-4">Beege!</h1>
        <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Or Bryan Berry if you want to be boring and legal</p>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-text-muted max-w-2xl mb-8">
          Engineering leader, builder, and community organizer based in Seoul.
        </p>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <a href="#contact" class="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-dark px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors">
            Get in touch
          </a>
          <a href="#professional-projects" class="border border-white/20 hover:border-white/40 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors">
            See my work
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="w-48 md:w-64 flex-shrink-0 order-1 md:order-2">
        <Image src={profileImage} alt="Photo of Beege" width={256} height={256}
          class="w-full rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary/50" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- About -->
  <Section id="about" title="About">
    <div class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl space-y-4">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer and engineering leader who's spent the last 15 years building things, 9 of which in Seoul. I've worked across gaming, insurance, AI, and medical tech — from Riot Games to PUBG to Lunit, where I led teams building annotation and data management tools for cancer detection AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like building things that matter, leading teams that ship, and teaching people who want to learn. I founded CodeSeoul to give developers in Seoul a place to grow, and I'm currently building a startup while exploring medical AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        Georgia Tech grad (Computational Media). American expat. Fluent in English, working on Korean.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Professional Projects -->
  <Section id="professional-projects" title="Professional Projects">
    <div class="space-y-16">

      <ProjectCard
        title="Data Management System"
        company="Lunit"
        roles={["Product Manager", "Project Manager"]}
        teamSize="6"
        highlight="300 TPS sustained in production"
        tags={["PostgreSQL", "Python", "DICOM", "Github Actions", "Google Cloud Platform", "Hashicorp Terraform", "Kubernetes", "Scrum", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Centralized system for organizing DICOM metadata, file references, and clinical study data — the first successful effort to get all the data in one place for annotation and ML training. Ideated the original system and led product management, delivering features including manufacturer aliasing, acquisition project tracking, and versioned ML splits for EU AI Act reproducibility. Centralized ingestion also uncovered and resolved data quality and duplication issues.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Data Pipeline Platform"
        company="Lunit"
        roles={["Project Manager"]}
        teamSize="6 data engineers"
        highlight="Reduced one inference task from 2 months to under 24 hours"
        tags={["PostgreSQL", "Python", "Prefect", "DICOM", "Github Actions", "Google Cloud Platform", "Hashicorp Terraform", "Kubernetes", "Scrum", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Massively concurrent pipeline for ingesting medical imaging data, preparing annotation datasets, and running bulk inference with in-house AI models. Conceived the original idea and built the proof of concept using Prefect before handing off to the team. Routinely processed hundreds of terabytes using spot instances and tuned autoscaling.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Oncology Annotation Tool"
        company="Lunit"
        roles={["Product Manager", "Project Manager", "DevOps Engineer", "Engineering Manager"]}
        teamSize="7"
        tags={["PostgreSQL", "Python", "Django", "MessagePack", "WebGL", "Github Actions", "Google Cloud Platform", "Hashicorp Terraform", "Kubernetes", "Scrum", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Internal tool for oncologists to label pathology whole slide images for cancer detection AI training, supporting distinct annotation modes — painting tissue areas, designating points, drawing cell contours, and sub-cellular labeling — on deeply zoomable WSIs. External contractor access with manager permissions enabled Lunit to scale annotation beyond its internal team.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Radiology Annotation Tool"
        company="Lunit"
        roles={["Product Manager", "Project Manager", "DevOps Engineer", "Backend Engineer", "Engineering Manager"]}
        teamSize="6"
        highlight="&ldquo;This is the smoothest annotation has ever gone.&rdquo;"
        tags={["MongoDB", "Python", "FastAPI", "DICOM", "Cornerstone", "Github Actions", "Amazon Web Services", "Google Cloud Platform", "Hashicorp Terraform", "Kubernetes", "Scrum", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Internal tool for radiologists to label medical images across chest X-rays, mammograms, and digital breast tomosynthesis, with queue-based and pool-based assignment and keyboard-shortcut-driven annotation. Took over as product manager and engineering manager. Introduced DBT modality support, multi-window current-prior comparison, cross-image annotation grouping, a reviewer feedback system, and an ML researcher API.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Command and Control System"
        company="Posicube"
        companyContext="Small startup (9–20 employees)"
        roles={["Backend Engineer", "Engineering Manager"]}
        tags={["Golang", "Web Sockets", "Gitlab CI", "On-Premise", "Amazon Web Services", "Hashicorp Terraform", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Remote management system for monitoring and controlling edge devices deployed at client sites. Built WebSocket-over-TLS communication between central and edge nodes, with relay node support for client network segmentation. All remote functions explicitly defined to pass security audits.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Robi Backend (now robi T)"
        company="Posicube"
        companyContext="Small startup (9–20 employees)"
        roles={["Backend Engineer", "Engineering Manager"]}
        tags={["Javascript", "NodeJS", "Firestore", "Google DialogFlow", "Google Cloud Platform", "Amazon Web Services", "Hashicorp Consul", "Docker Swarm", "Kubernetes", "Hashicorp Terraform", "ElasticSearch", "Kibana", "DataDog", "Gitlab CI", "Agile Development"]}
      >
        <p>Backend for Robi, an AI-powered phone receptionist that routes callers to appropriate departments via Google DialogFlow for speech recognition, intent detection, and TTS. Architected the backend as a monorepo of six microservices controlled by feature flags.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Car Rental Service"
        company="SK TechX (SK Telecom)"
        roles={["Backend Engineer"]}
        tags={["Java", "Spring Boot", "Maven", "BitBucket"]}
      >
        <p>Service enabling users to reserve and autonomously access rental cars without human intervention. Developed backend reservation and vehicle access APIs as part of an 8-service Spring Boot platform.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Network Player Impact Report"
        company="Riot Games"
        roles={["Data Analyst"]}
        highlight="Wired players showed a statistically significant 1% win-rate increase after normalizing for all identifiable factors"
        tags={["Tableau", "Hadoop Hive"]}
      >
        <p>Team analysis examining whether League of Legends players had a meaningful win-rate change on wired vs. wireless connections. Contributed by querying petabytes of game and infrastructure data from Hadoop Hive; statistical analysis led by teammate. Findings delivered via Tableau dashboards.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Near Real-Time Service Monitoring"
        company="Riot Games"
        roles={["Data Engineer"]}
        tags={["Bash", "Python", "MySQL", "JMX"]}
      >
        <p>Minute-resolution metrics collection system feeding game server health data to the Network Operations Center. Built collectors for server availability, login queue size, and concurrent players across global infrastructure.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Splunk Expansion"
        company="Asurion"
        roles={["Monitoring Engineer"]}
        highlight="Reduced incident isolation time by 80%"
        tags={["Splunk", "Python"]}
      >
        <p>Expanded Splunk from an unmaintained audit tool into a core component of company-wide monitoring. Deployed across all infrastructure and worked with Splunk professional services to build operational dashboards.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="ETL Operations"
        company="Asurion"
        roles={["ETL Operations Engineer"]}
        tags={["SSIS", "Microsoft SQL Server", "PHP"]}
      >
        <p>Administered and developed a homebrewed SSIS-based ETL framework running 600+ active jobs for insurance claims processing. Managed critical workflows for customer data acquisition, claims, and fulfillment. Built a knowledge management system and helped manage an offshore team in India.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <OtherContributions entries={[
        {
          title: "Wordpress Deployment",
          company: "PUBG",
          role: "DevOps",
          summary: "Deployed Wordpress on AWS via Terraform to replace the company home page.",
          tags: ["AWS", "Terraform"]
        },
        {
          title: "Nagios Expansion",
          company: "Asurion Mobile Apps",
          role: "Monitoring",
          summary: "Expanded Nagios metrics and refined alerting to reduce noise.",
          tags: ["Nagios", "Python"]
        },
        {
          title: "Splunk Deployment",
          company: "Asurion Mobile Apps",
          role: "Monitoring",
          summary: "Green-field Splunk deployment with log aggregation, metric extraction, and dashboards.",
          tags: ["Splunk", "Python"]
        },
        {
          title: "Build System Prototype",
          company: "Asurion Mobile Apps",
          role: "Monitoring",
          summary: "Prototyped build system migration from legacy Perl to Ruby on Rails; deployed after departure.",
          tags: ["Ruby", "Rails"]
        },
        {
          title: "Single Pane of Glass",
          company: "Asurion",
          role: "Monitoring",
          summary: "Deployed CA Spectrum and CA eHealth to overhaul the NOC with CA professional services.",
          tags: ["CA Spectrum", "CA eHealth"]
        }
      ]} />

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Personal Projects -->
  <Section id="personal-projects" title="Personal Projects">
    <div class="space-y-16">

      <ProjectCard
        title="VizPlan"
        links={[{ label: "Live", url: "https://vizplan.app" }]}
        images={[
          { src: "/vizplan1.png", alt: "VizPlan landing page showing 'Plan Your Work From Vision to Action' headline with an isometric node visualization" },
          { src: "/vizplan2.png", alt: "VizPlan hierarchical tree view with nested task cards showing priority levels and roll-up progress" },
          { src: "/vizplan3.png", alt: "VizPlan team settings page showing member management and API key configuration" }
        ]}
        tags={["Next.js", "TypeScript", "Supabase", "SaaS", "Model-Context Protocol", "PostgreSQL"]}
      >
        <p>A SaaS tool for leaders to visualize alignment between company goals and the work teams are actually doing, identify bottlenecks and risks, and manage workload capacity. Connects to project management tools (Jira, Linear, etc.) and surfaces where planned work drifts from strategic objectives — giving leaders real visibility without micromanaging. Designed with a bidirectional sync strategy to meet teams where they already work.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="MedDaaS"
        links={[
          { label: "Live", url: "https://meddaas.beege.works" },
          { label: "GitHub", url: "https://github.com/CodeSeoul/MedDaaS" }
        ]}
        images={[
          { src: "/meddaas1.png", alt: "MedDaaS homepage with search bar and progress card showing a score of 62.9/100 with 2 reports completed" },
          { src: "/meddaas2.png", alt: "MedDaaS reporting interface showing a chest X-ray with brightness and contrast controls alongside a report text editor" },
          { src: "/medaas3.png", alt: "MedDaaS detailed feedback page with scoring breakdown for similarity, completeness, accuracy, and terminology" }
        ]}
        tags={["FastAPI", "Python", "LLM / RAG", "PostgreSQL", "SpoonAI SDK"]}
      >
        <p>An AI-powered radiology training platform that helps medical students and radiologists sharpen their diagnostic skills. Students write diagnostic reports for chest X-rays, and the system compares them against expert ground truth using multi-step LLM analysis — delivering finding-by-finding scoring, educational feedback, and actionable improvement suggestions in real time via streaming. Built for the Spoon OS hackathon with CodeSeoul.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="AI Fix Assist"
        tags={["Python", "LLM Inference", "Medical AI", "Self-Hosted", "Agent Tooling", "RAG", "PGVector"]}
      >
        <p>A web app for assisting medical imaging device technicians in China. Designed to run models like Qwen on local infrastructure or with remote models like Claude. Uses agent tools to lookup repair guidance documentation via RAG and web search.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

      <ProjectCard
        title="Monster Brawl"
        tags={["Lua", "CoronaSDK", "Python", "Twisted Matrix"]}
      >
        <p>Turn-based battle game where players would pit classic monsters against each other. Included account management, matchmaking, gameplay, and stats. Never released.</p>
      </ProjectCard>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Professional Experience -->
  <Section id="professional-experience" title="Professional Experience">
    <div class="space-y-10">

      <!-- Lunit -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Product Management Team Lead, AI Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Lunit — Gangnam-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">August 2022 – October 2025 (3 years, 2 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Planned and implemented the first database for radiology products' training and validation data, covering petabytes of data, improving data management efficiency and regulatory compliance.</li>
          <li>Coordinated data model redesign and de-duplication logic to reduce manual efforts across data ingestion.</li>
          <li>Defined and implemented a data usage management system to mitigate risk of data leakage in the AI model development process.</li>
          <li>Expanded product management capabilities by hiring 2 PMs, 1 program manager, 2 designers, and 1 QA engineer.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">AI Platform Team Lead</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Lunit — Gangnam-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">September 2021 – August 2022 (11 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Led team to improve annotation project flow, lauded by customers as "the smoothest annotation projects have ever gone."</li>
          <li>Added 2.5D image modality support to the image annotation tool.</li>
          <li>Expanded the team by hiring a DevOps engineer, backend engineering lead, backend engineer, and MLOps engineering lead.</li>
          <li>Designed and led implementation of hierarchical data labels, contour annotations, reviewer system, progress visualization, and bad data reporting.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Senior Back-end Engineer / DevOps Engineer</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Lunit — Gangnam-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">January 2021 – September 2021 (8 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Built CI/CD system on BuildKite for the training data annotation system.</li>
          <li>Refactored FastAPI services to better follow microservice architecture.</li>
          <li>Configured Kubernetes deployment on AWS EKS (Terraform) and baremetal (Ansible).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Posicube -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Back-end Engineer / DevOps / Team Lead</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Posicube — Seocho-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">September 2018 – December 2020 (2 years, 3 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Built back-end services for AI-driven phone reception product and online delivery product in NodeJS on AWS Lambda and GCP Kubernetes.</li>
          <li>Led back-end team of 4 engineers building MSA-compatible monorepo for IoT-to-AI communication.</li>
          <li>Designed and managed infrastructure in AWS and GCP using Terraform. Set up ELK logging on GCP Kubernetes.</li>
          <li>Built remote control service for field Raspberry Pi devices using Golang on AWS ECS.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- PUBG -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Back-end Engineer</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">PUBG Corporation — Seocho-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">November 2017 – July 2018 (8 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Developed microservices using Go and C#. Automated infrastructure with Terraform.</li>
          <li>Built data pipelines for public API service and ML systems using AWS Lambda, SQS, S3, Redshift, and Kinesis.</li>
          <li>Delivered public API service written in Go, running on AWS ECS.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- SK Tech X -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Back-end Engineer</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">SK Tech X — Gangnam-gu, Seoul</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">January 2017 – November 2017 (10 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Worked on service platform built on Spring consisting of 8 services.</li>
          <li>Refactored build pipeline, reducing local build time from 7+ minutes to under 2 minutes.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Riot Games -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Live Data Analyst</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Riot Games — Santa Monica, CA</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">October 2013 – September 2016 (2 years, 11 months)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Developed and maintained near-real-time, international data collection systems at minute-resolution for 100+ metrics using Bash, Python, and Go.</li>
          <li>Created Tableau reports on client network performance and game health metrics using Hadoop Hive data from millions of players globally.</li>
          <li>Developed a player impact REST API in Go deployed on Docker, exposing abnormal metric values around the player experience.</li>
          <li>Designed and taught a Python basics class to NOC Technicians.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Chainsaw Rabbit -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Co-founder & Developer</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Chainsaw Rabbit Games — San Francisco, CA</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">November 2012 – June 2015 (part-time)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Co-designed asynchronous, competitive, multi-platform mobile game.</li>
          <li>Created game client in Lua/CoronaSDK and Python-based game server using Twisted Matrix.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Asurion -->
      <div class="border-l-2 border-white/30 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Production Systems Analyst → Analyst II</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Asurion — San Francisco, CA → Nashville, TN</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-3">August 2010 – October 2013 (3 years)</p>
        <ul class="text-text-muted space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm">
          <li>Implemented distributed Splunk infrastructure from the ground up. Reduced incident isolation time by 80%.</li>
          <li>Administered homebrewed SSIS-based ETL framework of 600+ active jobs.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Education -->
      <div class="mt-12 border-l-2 border-primary/50 pl-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">B.S. Computational Media</h3>
        <p class="text-primary text-sm mb-1">Georgia Institute of Technology</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">2006 – 2011</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Community -->
  <Section id="community" title="Community">
    <div class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-3xl space-y-4">
      <p>
        I founded <a href="https://www.meetup.com/codeseoul/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">CodeSeoul</a> in 2016 — a non-profit developer community in Seoul with 3,400+ members on Meetup, averaging 40 attendees per event. We run coding classes, hackathons, career workshops, and more.
      </p>
      <p>
        Check us out on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@codeseoul" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">YouTube</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <Section id="contact" title="Get in Touch">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <!-- Social & Professional -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6">
